title: [Roblox] - Tadachii's Force Close Game Script
content:
--When pressing "CTRL" + "L" this will "leave" the game by "force closing it", or shutting down the game. This only happens for you, other players will still stay in the game.

--I made this script mainly for when games are overly laggy, they freeze, something happens to where the game becomes unplayable or someone is exploiting the game, and is preventing me from doing certain actions.

-- Function to handle forcefully closing Roblox
local function forceCloseRoblox()
    game:Shutdown()
end

-- Bind the function to the keyboard input (CTRL + L)
game:GetService("UserInputService").InputBegan:Connect(function(input, isProcessed)
    if isProcessed then
        return
    end

    if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.L and game:GetService("UserInputService"):IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.LeftControl) then
        forceCloseRoblox()
    end
end)

content:
--This script was made for you to be able to kill/"reset" your character if resetting your character is not an option, or has 
--been taken out. This script will also work as a suicide command.

-- Function to handle player's death
local function forceResetAction()
    local player = game.Players.LocalPlayer
    if player.Character and player.Character:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") then
        player.Character.Humanoid.Health = 0
    end
end

-- Bind the function to a keyboard input (e.g., press 'K' to kill)
game:GetService("UserInputService").InputBegan:Connect(function(input, isProcessed)
    if isProcessed then
        return
    end

    if input.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.K then
        forceResetAction()
    end
end)

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.ticker import MultipleLocator
from astropy.time import Time
from astropy.timeseries import LombScargle

# Read data from the combined file "jd_mag_control.DAT"
data_combined = np.loadtxt('jd_mag_control.DAT')

# Extract Julian date, asteroid magnitude, and control star magnitude columns
julian_dates_asteroid = data_combined[:, 0]
magnitudes_asteroid = data_combined[:, 1]
magnitudes_control = data_combined[:, 2]

# Convert Julian dates to Astropy Time objects
time_asteroid = Time(julian_dates_asteroid, format='jd')

# Calculate the time difference in hours between each data point and a reference time
time_diff_hours_asteroid = (time_asteroid - time_asteroid[0]).to_value('h')

# Convert the minimum and maximum periods to hours
min_period_days = 0.01
max_period_days = 0.5
min_period_hours = min_period_days * 24
max_period_hours = max_period_days * 24

# Higher precision Lomb-Scargle periodogram within the specified period range
n_frequency = 1_000_000  # Increase the number of frequencies for higher precision
frequencies = np.linspace(1.0 / max_period_hours, 1.0 / min_period_hours, n_frequency)

# Calculate the Lomb-Scargle periodogram with higher precision for asteroid data
power_asteroid = LombScargle(time_diff_hours_asteroid, magnitudes_asteroid).power(frequencies, method='fast',
                                                                                  normalization='psd')

# Find the dominant period within the specified period range for asteroid data (highest peak in the periodogram)
dominant_frequency_asteroid = frequencies[np.argmax(power_asteroid)]
dominant_period_hours_asteroid = 1.0 / dominant_frequency_asteroid

# Calculate the double period for asteroid data
double_frequency_asteroid = dominant_frequency_asteroid / 2.0
double_period_hours_asteroid = 1.0 / double_frequency_asteroid

# Estimate the error in the double period (standard deviation of the peaks near the dominant frequency)
peak_indices = np.argpartition(power_asteroid, -5)[-5:]  # Consider the top 5 peaks in the periodogram
double_period_errors = np.std(1.0 / frequencies[peak_indices] / 2.0)

# Set up the plot
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))

# Plot the observed light curve for the asteroid
plt.scatter(time_diff_hours_asteroid, magnitudes_asteroid, label='Asteroid 6249', marker='o', color='blue', s=10)

# Plot vertical lines at the end of the dominant and double periods for the asteroid
end_period_time_asteroid = time_diff_hours_asteroid[0] + dominant_period_hours_asteroid
end_double_period_time_asteroid = time_diff_hours_asteroid[0] + double_period_hours_asteroid
plt.axvline(end_period_time_asteroid, color='green', linestyle='--',
            label=f'Dominant Period (Asteroid): {dominant_period_hours_asteroid:.6f} hours')
plt.axvline(end_double_period_time_asteroid, color='orange', linestyle='--',
            label=f'Double Period (Asteroid): {double_period_hours_asteroid:.6f} hours')

# Format the plot
plt.xlabel('Time (hours)', fontsize=14)
plt.ylabel('Magnitude', fontsize=14)
plt.title('Light Curve Analysis for Asteroid 6249', fontsize=16)
plt.legend(loc='upper right', fontsize=12)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)

# Invert the Y-axis
plt.gca().invert_yaxis()

# Set major locator for X-axis to show more hour values
major_locator = MultipleLocator(base=1)
minor_locator = MultipleLocator(base=0.5)
plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(major_locator)
plt.gca().xaxis.set_minor_locator(minor_locator)

# Use LaTeX for better typesetting of labels
plt.rc('text', usetex=True)
plt.rc('font', family='serif')

plt.show()

# Print the double period with its error
print(f"Dominant Period (Asteroid): {dominant_period_hours_asteroid:.6f} hours")
print(f"Double Period (Asteroid): {double_period_hours_asteroid:.6f} hours (+- {double_period_errors:.6f} hours)")

import time
import json
from datetime import datetime
from logging import Logger
from lib.kafka_connect import KafkaConsumer, KafkaProducer
from lib.redis import RedisClient
from stg_loader.repository import StgRepository

class StgMessageProcessor:
    def __init__(self,
                 consumer: KafkaConsumer,
                 producer: KafkaProducer,
                 redis: RedisClient,
                 stg_repository: StgRepository,
                 batch_size: int,
                 logger: Logger) -> None:
        self._consumer = consumer
        self._producer = producer
        self._redis = redis
        self._stg_repository = stg_repository
        self._batch_size = batch_size
        self._logger = logger

    # функция, которая будет вызываться по расписанию.
    def run(self) -> None:
        # Пишем в лог, что джоб был запущен.
        self._logger.info(f"{datetime.utcnow()}: START")

        for _ in range(self._batch_size):
            msg = self._consumer.consume()
            self._logger.info(msg)
            print(msg)
            if not msg:
                self._logger.info(f"{datetime.utcnow()}: There is no message")   
                break

            payload = msg['payload']

            self._stg_repository.order_events_insert(msg['object_id'], msg['object_type'], msg['sent_dttm'], json.dumps(payload))
            user_id = payload['user']['id']
            restaurant_id = payload['restaurant']['id']

            products = []

            for product in payload['order_items']:
                products.append(
                    {
                        'id':product['id'],
                        'name':product['name'],
                        'price':product['price'],
                        'quantity':product['quantity']
                    }
                )

            out_message = {
                'object_id':msg['object_id'],
                'object_type':msg['object_type'], 
                'sent_dttm':msg['sent_dttm'],
                'payload':msg['payload'],
                'date':payload['date'],
                'cost':payload['cost'],
                'payment':payload['payment'],
                'status':payload['final_status'],
                'restaurant':{
                    'id': restaurant_id,
                    'name':self._redis.get(restaurant_id)
                },
                'user':{
                    'id':user_id,
                    'name':self._redis.get(user_id)
                },
                'products':products

            }

            self._producer.produce(out_message)

        # Пишем в лог, что джоб успешно завершен.
        self._logger.info(f"{datetime.utcnow()}: FINISH")

title: Python enum str
content:
# 31.07.23

'''
Good way to write enums in python is
to inherite enum class from str and Enum.
In that case you can compare enum objects
with strings.
'''

from enum import Enum

class IPhone(str, Enum):
    IPhone11 = 'iphone11'
    IPhone12 = 'iphone12'
    IPhone13 = 'iphone13'
    IPhone14 = 'iphone14'

print(IPhone.IPhone11 == 'iphone11')
# True

print("Welcome to the Simple Calculator!")

while True:
    print('\nSelect an operation:')
    print('1. Addition')
    print('2. Subtraction')
    print('3. Multiplication')
    print('4. Division')
    print('5. Exit')

    choice = input('Enter the operation number (1/2/3/4/5): ')

    if choice == '5':
        print('Thank you for using the calculator. Goodbye!')
        break

    if choice not in ['1', '2', '3', '4', '5']:
        print('Invalid input. Please try again.')
        continue

    num1 = float(input('Enter the first number: '))
    num2 = float(input('Enter the second number: '))

    if choice == '1':
        result = num1 + num2
        print(f'{num1} + {num2} = {result}')

    elif choice == '2':
        result = num1 - num2
        print(f'{num1} - {num2} = {result}')

    elif choice == '3':
        result = num1 * num2
        print(f'{num1} * {num2} = {result}')

    elif choice == '4':
        if num2 == 0:
            print('Error: Cannot divide by zero!')
        else:
            result = num1 / num2
            print(f'{num1} / {num2} = {result}')

#!/usr/bin/env python3
import readline
import asyncio
import threading
from threading import Thread
import sys

command_queue = asyncio.Queue()

def stderr_print(*args, **kwargs):
    print(*args, file=sys.stderr, **kwargs)


def shutdown_threads():
    for task in asyncio.all_tasks():
        task.cancel()


def queue_console_input(chunk):
    command_queue.put_nowait(chunk)


async def handle_console_input(loop, done):
    while not done.is_set():
        chunk = await command_queue.get()
        stderr_print("got chunk: \"%s\"" % chunk)
        if chunk == 'quit':
            print("quit handled")
            done.set()


def console_loop(loop, done):
    try:
        loop.run_until_complete(handle_console_input(loop, done))
        stderr_print("completed")
    except asyncio.CancelledError:
        loop.close()
        stderr_print("loop closed")
        done.set()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()
    console_done = threading.Event()
    console_thread = Thread(target=console_loop, args=(loop,console_done))
    console_thread.daemon = True
    console_thread.start()
    print("thread started")
    try:
        counter = 1
        while not console_done.is_set():
            chunk = input(f"{counter} console> ")

title: Threading PITA v2
content:
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import readline
import asyncio
import threading
from threading import Thread
import sys
import os

command_queue = asyncio.Queue()

def stderr_print(*args, **kwargs):
    print(*args, file=sys.stderr, **kwargs)


def shutdown_threads():
    for task in asyncio.all_tasks():
        task.cancel()


def queue_console_input(chunk):
    command_queue.put_nowait(chunk)


async def handle_console_input(loop, done):
    while not done.is_set():
        chunk = await command_queue.get()
        stderr_print("got chunk: \"%s\"" % chunk)
        if chunk == 'quit':
                print("quit handled")
                done.set()


def command_console(loop, done):
    try:
        counter = 1
        while not done.is_set():
            chunk = input(f"{counter} console> ")
            print(f"{counter} got input {chunk}")
            loop.call_soon_threadsafe(queue_console_input, chunk)
            if chunk == 'quit':
                print(f"{counter} quit detected")
                done.set()
            counter += 1
    except KeyboardInterrupt:
        stderr_print("THREAD Got INTERRUPT!")
        loop.call_soon_threadsafe(shutdown_threads)
        console_thread.join()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    loop = asyncio.get_event_loop()
    console_done = threading.Event()
    console_thread = Thread(target=command_console, args=(loop, console_done))
    console_thread.daemon = True
    console_thread.start()
    print("thread started")
    print("entering asyncio loop")
    try:
        loop.run_until_complete(handle_console_input(loop, console_done))
        loop.call_soon_threadsafe(shutdown_threads)
        console_thread.join(0)
    except KeyboardInterrupt:
        stderr_print("Got INTERRUPT!")
        console_done.set()
        loop.call_soon_threadsafe(shutdown_threads)
        console_thread.join(0)
        os.system('/usr/bin/reset')
    print("done")

select soc.user_id,
       c.payment_type,
       c.flag_card,
       soi.price,
       soi.payment_date,
       soi.send_date,
       sop.payment_type,
       sop.value,
       sop.discount,
       sop.quantity,
       soc.consumed,
       i.cart_item_id,
       i.price,
       i.send_date,
       i.installment,
       ci.last_invoice_status,
       ci.discount_price,
       c.status
from store_oneclick_invoice soi
         join store_oneclick_purchase sop on soi.store_oneclick_purchase_id = sop.id
         join store_oneclick_campaign soc on sop.oneclick_campaign_id = soc.id
         join invoice i on soi.invoice_id = i.id
         join cart_items ci on i.cart_item_id = ci.id
         join cart c on ci.id_cart = c.id
         join user u on c.user_id = u.id
where sop.quantity > 1
order by sop.created_at desc;
